version_description: Complete version with all the lyrics.
Added correct instrumental chord progression. Complete chord progression with key change.
Specific, corrected chords true to the key, labeled and timed sections, detailed notes, strumming pattern.
None of the chord versions has the 3rd verse right which uses a different chord sequence in second half and added in the breakdown at the end.....
Didn't find any others with this chord scheme, this is of the video https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wqqnxEmSOB4.

This is more for piano/keyboard players, however, you can just bar a standard Gmin chord and walk the bass line following my root/bass guides if you're trying to play solo. The other thing to note is that Matt Belamy generally sticks to the 2nd inversion on the Gm but throws in little licks to make it sound more interesting.
This version has the correct tuning: "Eb-Ab-Db-Gb-Bb-Eb" (Tuning is not the standard tuning in this song).
